Been there a few a times as I live not far. Last time, I was there, I ordered an appetizer, kept my tab open so that I could order a meal but the bartender told me I needed to order a drink in order to keep my seat at the bar? When I started to explain that I had ordered an appetizer, she interrupted me and therefore I gave up my seat. Yet, had no where to sit for when I was ordering my main course? I get it, they need seats for paying customers but when my total tab comes out more than the booze costing the guy I gave up my chair to, then common sense has been thrown out the window. Plenty of bars around to spend my money at without dealing with that nonsense.
